communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The hypothesis posited is that the immunological experience of CAR inhabitants is preventing outbreaks, even though the virus is circulating. It is possible, but more evidence is needed.

Is 10 per cent seroprevalence high, compared with that in the African countries that are suffering outbreaks? How does the prevalence and infection intensity in wildlife compare in CAR and in countries with epidemics?

The Ebola epidemic is clearly demonstrating the need for integrating disciplines such as epidemiology and disease ecology to be able to comprehend the dynamics of Ebola virus. Much research is needed. Only when a sound understanding of the mechanisms underlying the transmission dynamics of this disease is achieved will we be in a position to properly anticipate and control these devastating outbreaks. - Mod.PMB

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2748411,66.]
